## Review Notes

* The worksheet contains image references for geometric figures that could not be fully captured. Teachers should consult the original DOCX for exact diagrams.
* Students should verify that their height measurements are perpendicular to the base when calculating parallelogram areas.
* The formula [A = d1 * d2 / 2] applies to both rhombuses and kites since both have perpendicular diagonals that bisect each other.
* When solving real-world problems, students should identify the quadrilateral type first, then select the appropriate area formula.
